'''Rolled plate''' is a type of industrially produced [[glass]]. It was invented and patented by [[James Hartley (inventor)|James Hartley]] circa 1847.<ref name="James Hartley">{{cite web |title=James Hartley |url=https://www.gracesguide.co.uk/James_Hartley |website=Grace's Guide to British Industrial History |accessdate=14 August 2018 |ref=James Hartley}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Glass Timeline |url=http://www.historyofglass.com/glass-history/glass-timeline/ |website=History of Glass |accessdate=14 August 2018 |ref=History_Timeline}}</ref> Rolled plate is used [[Architectural glass|architecturally]]; for example, in the mid-19th century uses for rolled plate glass included roofing railway stations and greenhouses.<ref name="James Hartley" />
